VARIATION
OF
THE
DISPERSION
OF
RADIO
WHISTLERS
DURING
MAGNETIC
STORMS
THE
WHISTLER
DISPERSION
SHOWS
A
SPECIAL
DECREASE
AT
POITIERS
AFTER
THE
COMMENCEMENT
OF
AN
INTENSE
MAGNETIC
STORM
THE
DECREASE
IS
NOT
OBSERVED
FOR
LESSER
STORMS
THIS
IS
POSSIBLY
DUE
TO
THE
EXISTENCE
OF
FAVOURED
PATHS
WHICH
MOVE
TO
LOWER
LATITUDES
AS
THE
STORM
INTENSITY
INCREASES
